"Member, missy, yes, Juner much 'member. Juner big gal when Juner com' 'way; 
when dey put Juner 'pon dat big hous' 'pon top o' de water, whar Juner neber tun 
roun'."


"Take for him, sir!" said the Doctor with vehemence; 
"why, sir, all the money in Mississippi couldn't buy him. I would just as soon think 
of cutting off my right hand, as of selling Robin."


"Madam, if Tom had stay where he was, dis thing never wou'd bin com' 'pon him; 
he'd bin well now, madam, an' look mighty diff'rent from what de poo' cretur look 
now."
